## 1. Current State

- Each prompt has a single **Category** label, auto-generated by AI during prompt creation
- Categories are display-only — no filtering, no editing, no user control
- Categories appear as labels next to prompts in the Manage Prompts tab
- Examples: "Disaster Recovery Services", "Managed Services", "Colocation Services"

---

## 2. Core Change: Single Category → Multi-Tag System

Prompts can now have **multiple tags** (replacing the single "category"). Tags enable **cluster-based reporting** — users can filter the dashboard and analytics by any tag to see aggregated metrics for just that subset of prompts.

**Why this matters:** Marketing departments in large companies need to report performance by specific angles — product lines, audience segments, use cases, campaigns, etc. Multi-tagging makes this possible.

**Example:**

| Prompt | Tags |
|--------|------|
| "What is the best life insurance for young adults?" | `life insurance`, `young adults` |
| "What is the best medical card for young adults?" | `medical insurance`, `young adults` |
| "What is the best life insurance for families in Malaysia?" | `life insurance`, `families` |

→ Filter by `young adults` → see prompts 1 & 2
→ Filter by `life insurance` → see prompts 1 & 3
→ Filter by `medical insurance` → see prompt 2 only

